==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tinned
<hw>Tinned</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Covered, or
plated, with tin; <as>as, a <ex>tinned</ex> roof; <ex>tinned</ex>
iron</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Packed in tin cases; canned; <as>as, <ex>tinned</ex>
meats</as>.</def> <rj><au>Cassell (Dict. of Cookery).</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tinnen</ent>⟦br⟧
